docs.summary: Shipping Options & Rates for Wix Stores

params.name: items
params.doc:
All items included to be sent
TODO change to 300 once cart limit will be 300

params.name: shippingOrigin
params.doc:
Where the items are sent from - this may be needed for some carriers.
 For now it will simply be the business location of the store.

params.name: currency
params.doc: Currency requested for the shipping rates

params.name: instanceId
params.doc: Instance id of the app that is called for the shipping rates

params.name: shippingRateDecimalPlaces
params.doc:
Expected decimal places for the shipping rate. For example, if this field is 2 then the shipping rate could be: 10$, 10.1$, 10.12$ (up until 2 decimal places).
 However it can **not** be: 10.123$ (or further), and in this case the shipping option will be ignored and not provided to the user.
 When not provided, the fraction size can be anything.

docs.summary: Used for grouping line items and is sent on add to cart

members.name: catalogItemId
members.doc: ID of the item within its Wix or 3rd-party catalog. For example, `productId` for Wix Stores or `eventId` for Wix Events.

members.name: appId
members.doc: ID of the catalog app. For example, the Wix Stores `appId`, or the 3rd-party `appId`.

members.name: options
members.doc: Additional info in key:value form. For example, `{"options":{"Size": "M", "Color": "Red"}}` or `{"variantId": "<VARIANT_ID>"}`.

members.name: weight
members.doc: Line item weight. Measurement unit (KG or LB) is taken from `order.weightUnit`.

members.name: sku
members.doc: Stock-keeping unit. Learn more about [SKUs](https://www.wix.com/encyclopedia/definition/stock-keeping-unit-sku).

members.name: shippable
members.doc: Whether this line item is shippable.

members.name: country
members.doc: Country code.

members.name: subdivision
members.doc: Subdivision. Usually a state, region, prefecture, or province code, according to [ISO 3166-2](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_3166-2).

members.name: city
members.doc: City name.

members.name: postalCode
members.doc: Zip/postal code.

members.name: addressLine2
members.doc: Free text providing more detailed address info. Usually contains Apt, Suite, and Floor.

members.name: streetAddress
members.doc: Street name and number.

members.name: addressLine
members.doc: Main address line, usually street and number as free text.

members.name: code
members.doc: Short subdivision code.

members.name: name
members.doc: Subdivision full name.

members.name: number
members.doc: Street number.

members.name: name
members.doc: Street name.

Unique code of provided shipping option like "usps_std_overnight".
 For legacy calculators this would be the UUID of the option.

Title of the option, such as USPS Standard Overnight Delivery (in the requested locale)

members.name: name

members.name: quantity

members.name: applicationError

docs.summary:
tax info types Possible values are:
  • UNSPECIFIED
  • CPF - CPF - for individual tax payers
  • CNPJ - CNPJ - for corporations

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_SUBDIVISION_TYPE
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_1 - State
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_2 - County
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_3 - City/town
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_4 - Neighborhood/quarter
  • ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_5 - Street/block
  • COUNTRY - ADMINISTRATIVE_AREA_LEVEL_0. Indicates the national political entity, and is typically the highest order type returned by the Geocoder.

Possible values are:
  • VALIDATION
  • OTHER
  • MAX
  • MIN
  • MAX_LENGTH
  • MIN_LENGTH
  • MAX_SIZE
  • MIN_SIZE
  • FORMAT
  • DECIMAL_LTE
  • DECIMAL_GTE
  • DECIMAL_LT
  • DECIMAL_GT
  • DECIMAL_MAX_SCALE
  • INVALID_ENUM_VALUE
  • REQUIRED_FIELD

Possible values are:
  • HANDLING_FEE

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_METHOD
  • STORE_PICKUP
  • PICKUP_POINT

Possible values are:
  • UNSPECIFIED_WEIGHT_UNIT - Weight unit can't be classified, due to an error
  • KG - Kilograms
  • LB - Pounds

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • ENABLED
  • DISABLED
  • PENDING
  • DEMO

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN
  • TRASH
  • DELETED
  • PENDING_PURGE

Possible values are:
  • UNKNOWN_NAMESPACE
  • WIX - Default namespace for UGC sites. MetaSites with this namespace will be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • SHOUT_OUT - ShoutOut stand alone product. These are siteless (no actual Wix site, no HtmlWeb). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • ALBUMS - MetaSites created by the Albums product, they appear as part of the Albums app. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • WIX_STORES_TEST_DRIVE - Part of the WixStores migration flow, a user tries to migrate and gets this site to view and if the user likes it then stores removes this namespace and deletes the old site with the old stores. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • HOTELS - Hotels standalone (siteless). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • CLUBS - Clubs siteless MetaSites, a club without a wix website. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • ONBOARDING_DRAFT - A partially created ADI website. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • DEV_SITE - AppBuilder for AppStudio / shmite (c). MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • LOGOS - LogoMaker websites offered to the user after logo purchase. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • VIDEO_MAKER - VideoMaker websites offered to the user after video purchase. MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • PARTNER_DASHBOARD - MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • DEV_CENTER_COMPANY - MetaSites with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • HTML_DRAFT - A draft created by HTML editor on open. Upon "first save" it will be moved to be of WIX domain. Meta site with this namespace will *not* be shown in a user's site list by default.
  • SITELESS_BUSINESS - the user-journey for Fitness users who want to start from managing their business instead of designing their website. Will be accessible from Site List and will not have a website app. Once the user attaches a site, the site will become a regular wixsite.
  • CREATOR_ECONOMY - Belongs to "strategic products" company. Supports new product in the creator's economy space.
  • DASHBOARD_FIRST - * It is to be used in the Business First efforts.
  • ANYWHERE - * Bookings business flow with no site.

Possible values are:
  • OTHER - A valid option, we don't expose all reasons why site might be created.
  • FROM_TEMPLATE - A meta site was created from template.
  • DUPLICATE_BY_SITE_TRANSFER - A meta site was created by copying of the transfferred meta site.
  • DUPLICATE - A copy of existing meta site.
  • OLD_SITE_TRANSFER - A meta site was created as a transfferred site (copy of the original), old flow, should die soon.
  • FLASH - deprecated A meta site was created for Flash editor.
